I’ve finished the audit. The implementation will touch four places only: shared PRD readiness checks, canonical PRD-to-draft conversion, API handlers for `/v1/ingress/prd` and document build, and `smithctl` submit/create error handling so canonical JSON and validation failures stay aligned.

Planned edits:
1. Extend shared PRD validation with a stable oversized-story diagnostic so readiness can fail before ingress.
2. Convert validated canonical PRDs into loop drafts, and reuse that from API ingress and document build instead of the old markdown/tasks shortcut.
3. Validate `workspace_prd_json` in `/v1/loops` before any loop record is created, and return structured validation payloads on 422s.
4. Update `smithctl` to submit canonical PRD JSON, preserve validation bodies on failure, and add targeted tests for API acceptance, rejection, and CLI/API parity.
